The paper deals with the problem of recovering a signal from random Gaussian projections, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The signal of interest is a superposition of complex exponential functions, which is a common signal model in many fields, including imaging science and NMR spectroscopy. The paper also uses low-rank Hankel matrix reconstruction, which is a technique commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper provides theoretical guidance on non-uniform sampling in NMR spectroscopy, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
